type: web_research
title: OpenClaw + LINE + MCP + AWS Round 2 Verification Research
key_insights[18]: "OpenClaw has 135K+ GitHub stars, Docker+Kubernetes deployment well-documented, Helm chart available","LINE is a PLUGIN channel in OpenClaw (not built-in), requires separate installation","openclaw-mcp-adapter v0.1.1 released 2026-02-03, solves cold-start problem (2.4s per MCP call without it)","OpenClaw native MCP support still pending (PR #5121 closed, issue #4834 open)","Claude Agent SDK renamed from Claude Code SDK, supports ephemeral/long-running/resumable container patterns",LINE webhook MUST respond with 2xx within 2 SECONDS - critical constraint for AI agent architecture,"LINE reply token expires in ~1 minute, can only be used once","Recommended LINE AI bot pattern: Reply with loading indicator immediately, then Push Message with AI response","OpenClaw security: 30K+ exposed instances, CVE-2026-25253 (RCE via WebSocket), CVE-2026-24763 (Docker sandbox injection)",Gartner warns against OpenClaw with 'unacceptable cybersecurity risk' language,"OpenClaw supports max 4 concurrent runs on main lane, 8 on subagent lane, Bull+Redis recommended for production queuing",OpenClaw base gateway needs ~300MB RAM + ~100MB per channel + sandbox overhead,"Smart model routing can cut costs 50%+ (Sonnet primary, Haiku fallback, Opus for complex only)","Cost range: $1-5/month light usage to $623/month unoptimized; containers ~$0.05/hour","LangGraph and OpenClaw are complementary, not competing - LangGraph for custom orchestration, OpenClaw for agent OS","Dify for RAG/AI prototyping, n8n for workflow automation, OpenClaw for autonomous agent - can combine all three","Claude Agent SDK WebSocket server implementations exist (claude-agent-server, claude-agent-kit)","LINE MCP server officially provided by LINE on GitHub, LY Corp tech blog documents implementation"
findings[12]: "CONFIRMED: OpenClaw Docker deployment is production-ready with well-documented guides","CONFIRMED: AWS deployment possible but most guides use EC2/Lightsail, NOT ECS Fargate specifically","CONFIRMED: openclaw-mcp-adapter exists and works but is very new (v0.1.1, Feb 2026)","CONTRADICTED: OpenClaw does NOT have native MCP support yet - adapter is community plugin","CONFIRMED: Claude Agent SDK is production-ready with official hosting docs","CRITICAL NEW: LINE 2-second webhook timeout makes synchronous AI response impossible","CRITICAL NEW: Multiple CVEs found for OpenClaw in Feb 2026 - security is immature","CONFIRMED: LINE MCP server exists officially from LINE/LY Corp","CONFIRMED: Multi-agent model routing is key cost optimization strategy","NEW: OpenClaw is designed as single-user/single-instance primarily, multi-user requires careful architecture","NEW: gVisor recommended for production sandbox hardening","NEW: Managed OpenClaw available on DigitalOcean App Platform with zero-downtime updates"
refs[12]: docs.openclaw.ai/install/docker - Official Docker deployment,docs.openclaw.ai/gateway/security - Security docs,docs.openclaw.ai/channels - Channel setup including LINE plugin,docs.openclaw.ai/concepts/multi-agent - Multi-agent routing,platform.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/hosting - Claude Agent SDK hosting,platform.claude.com/docs/en/agent-sdk/secure-deployment - Security deployment,developers.line.biz/en/docs/messaging-api/receiving-messages/ - LINE webhook 2s timeout,developers.line.biz/en/docs/messaging-api/sending-messages/ - Reply vs Push messages,techblog.lycorp.co.jp/en/introduction-to-mcp-and-building-mcp-server-using-line-messaging-api - LINE MCP server,github.com/androidStern-personal/openclaw-mcp-adapter - MCP adapter plugin,github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/4834 - Native MCP support request,penligent.ai - OpenClaw security hardening manifest
recommendations[7]: Option 2 (Claude Agent SDK backend) is SAFER than Option 1 (OpenClaw hub) due to OpenClaw security immaturity,"Option 3 (Hybrid) is BEST: Claude Agent SDK for LINE-facing backend + OpenClaw for internal agent tasks","LINE webhook handler MUST be async: Lambda receives webhook -> returns 200 immediately -> SQS -> Agent processes -> Push Message API",Use gVisor + Docker for any OpenClaw deployment in production,"Implement smart model routing: Haiku for simple, Sonnet for medium, Opus for complex tasks",Budget should account for $5-15/month API costs per active user plus infrastructure,Consider Dify or n8n as middleware alternatives if OpenClaw security concerns are blocking
